                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Bussel</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_109466">Samford</placeName>
                        </persName> 
               and <persName>
                           <forename>Mabilia</forename> his wife, daughter of <persName>
                              <forename>Ralph</forename>, the knight of <placeName role="person" key="place_109466">Samford</placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
               grant to the <orgName key="org_107016">church of St. Nicholas, Litlemore</orgName>, in frankalmoigne, one
               virgate of land, viz. 16 1/2 acres in the fields of <placeName key="place_109466">Samford</placeName>. 
               Witnesses. <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Turbervile</surname>, sheriff of <placeName role="sheriff" key="place_105449">Oxon</placeName>
                        </persName>,
               <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Wasthose</surname>
                        </persName> and many others. 
               Dated the morrow of St laurence, being Tuesday next before the feast of the Assumption, 
               <origDate when="1254">1254</origDate>, <origDate notBefore="1253-10-28" notAfter="1254-10-27">38 Hen. III</origDate>.</p>
